Very excellent, I enjoyed this quite a bit. Leaves a bunch of questions at the end but I do not mind that, really, with some exception.

If I were to have one critique, which is a critique I often have for very short scips like this, it feels as if there is not much  included in this that I would expect from the Foundation. For instance, did the Foundation go approach the genetic testing company that these letters came from? Did they go to the return address? Did they witness an occurrence of this phenomenon? How did they find out about it at all?

These are questions I feel like are left unanswered that I, personally, do not believe the Foundation would leave either unanswered or, at least, addressed to some degree.

Otherwise, this is very poignant as a little parable. Perhaps I should go plan a family reunion. :] +1





